All tests pass. Here's a summary of what was found and fixed:

---

## 🐛 The Needle: Event Listener Leak in `processor.js`

**Root Cause:** Inside `DataProcessor.process()`, two new event listeners were registered on the shared `eventBus` **on every single request**:
```js
// Called per-request — BUG
this.eventBus.on('data:validated', (validatedData) => { ... });
this.eventBus.on('data:error', (err) => { ... });
```
After 500 requests → 500+ listeners accumulated, each holding a closure over the request's `data` object, preventing garbage collection and leaking memory indefinitely.

**Fix:** Moved the listener registrations into the **constructor** so they are set up exactly once, regardless of how many requests are processed:
```js
constructor(eventBus) {
    // Registered once — no leak
    this.eventBus.on('data:validated', ...);
    this.eventBus.on('data:error', ...);
}
```

**Result:** Listener count stays at **2** (stable) after 500 requests, instead of growing to 1000+.
